article.description:
Shavonte Zellous scored 30 points to lead No.
24 Pittsburgh to its eighth straight victory, 81-61 over Providence
on Saturday.
article.headline: No. 24 Pittsburgh sprints to double-digit win over Providence
article.linkText: Zellous leads No. 24 Pitt to eighth straight victory
article.story:
PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Shavonte Zellous scored 30 points to lead Pittsburgh (No. 24 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) to its eighth straight victory, 81-61 over Providence on Saturday.

Marcedes Walker had 18 points and nine rebounds for Pitt (14-3, 4-0 Big East).

Freshman Mi-Khida Hankins finished with 16 points and eight rebounds for Providence (11-6, 1-3).

Providence raced to an early 9-8 lead before Pittsburgh went on a 22-9 run for a 30-18 lead at the break. Zellous had 13 first-half points, and Walker scored 10 by the break.

In the second half, Providence shot 14-for-30 from the field, including 3-for-8 from 3-point range, but the Panthers countered with 15-for-26 shooting to stretch their lead to the final 20-point margin.

Pittsburgh built a 38-29 rebounding edge in the win and defeated the Friars for the eighth time in 11 games. Providence leads 26-19 in the series.
